Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
ecoSplitComplexFlop(25.10)                          ecoSplitComplexFlop(25.10)

Name
       ecoSplitComplexFlop  -  Splits  a complex flip-flop into a simple flip-
       flop and combinational logic for the specified instance

Syntax
       ecoSplitComplexFlop

       [-help]

       [-force]

       {-inst {<inst1>, <inst2>,...} | -listFile <instNamesFile>| -all}

       [-legal]

       [-preCTS | -postCTS | -postRoute]

       [-power]

       [-skipRoute]

       Splits a complex flip-flop into a simple  flip-flop  and  combinational
       logic  for the specified instance. A complex flip-flop means the D side
       has some combinational logic, such as AND, OR, MUX, AOI, and so on.  By
       default,  a specific flip-flop is split only if equivalent simple flip-
       flops and combinational logic can be found in libraries  and  there  is
       timing gain or power gain after the split.

       You  can also specify that the split flip-flops should be placed in le-
       gal locations. By default, the positions of the  split  flip-flops  are
       not guaranteed to be legal.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each ecoSplitComplexFlop parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command:  man ecoSplitComplexFlop

       -all   Specifies  that  all  flop  instances  in  the  design should be
              processed.

              Note: The -inst, -listFile, and -all parameters are mutually ex-
              clusive. One of these parameters must be specified.

       -force When specified, forces the complex flip-flops to  split  regard-
              less of the timing gains.

       -inst {<inst1, inst2,...>}
              Specifies  the  names of the flop instances to be split. You can
              specify a single instance or a  tcl  list  of  instances  to  be
              split.

              Note: The -inst, -listFile, and -all parameters are mutually ex-
              clusive. One of these parameters must be specified.

       -listFile <instNamesFile>
              Specifies the file containing the names of the flop instances to
              be  split. Specify one instance on one line. Comment with #. In-
              stance name should not contain spaces or backslashes.

              Note: The -inst, -listFile, and -all parameters are mutually ex-
              clusive. One of these parameters must be specified.

       -legal When specified, places the split  flip-flops  and  combinational
              cells at a legal location.

       -preCTS
              Specify this parameter, if the design stage is preCTS.

       -postCTS
              Specify this parameter, if the design stage is postCTS.

       -postRoute
              Specify this parameter, if the design stage is postRoute.

       -power When specified, complex flops are split to reclaim power.

              By default, the flops are split for timing.

       -skipRoute
              Skip routing after split in postRoute stage.

Examples
              * Use  the  following  command  to force the flip-flop split for
                power for all instances during the preCTS stage.

                ecoSplitComplexFlop -force -preCTS -power -all

              * Use the following command for flip-flop split for  timing  for
                the instance ff1 during the preCTS stage.

                ecoSplitComplexFlop -inst ff1 -preCTS

